      <p><strong>{{ yearData.year }}</strong> is the <strong>Year of the {{ yearData.element }} {{ yearData.animal }}</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">{{ yearData.elementCn }}{{ yearData.animalCn }}</span>, {{ yearData.pillarCn }}) in the Chinese zodiac. This is a <strong>{{ yearData.yinYang }} {{ yearData.element }}</strong> year, governed by the Heavenly Stem <strong>{{ yearData.stem }}</strong> and the Earthly Branch <strong>{{ yearData.branch }} ({{ yearData.branchCn }})</strong>.</p>

      <p>In the sexagenary cycle (六十甲子), {{ yearData.year }} occupies position <strong>#{{ ((yearData.year - 4) % 60 + 60) % 60 + 1 }}</strong> of 60. The cycle has been used continuously since the Shang Dynasty (c. 1600 BCE) to count years, and it takes 60 years to complete one full revolution.</p>

      <p>In the traditional Chinese calendar, the zodiac year in BaZi (Four Pillars of Destiny) tradition starts at <strong>Lichun (立春)</strong>, the "Start of Spring" solar term, which typically falls on February 3rd, 4th, or 5th. People born before Lichun in {{ yearData.year }} belong to the previous zodiac year.</p>

      <div class="callout-box" style="margin:var(--sp-xl) 0;">
        <span class="callout-box-icon">🔮</span>
        <div class="callout-box-content">
