    <section id="element">
      <h2>{{ yearData.element }} Element ({{ yearData.elementCn }}) in {{ yearData.year }}</h2>
      <p>The {{ yearData.element }} element from the Heavenly Stem combines with the {{ yearData.animal }}'s <strong>fixed element of {{ yearData.fixedElement }} ({{ yearData.fixedElementCn }})</strong> to create the unique energy signature of {{ yearData.year }}. In Wu Xing (Five Elements) theory, these two elements interact through the generating (相生) and overcoming (相剋) cycles.</p>

      {% if yearData.element == yearData.fixedElement %}
      <p>Since the yearly element ({{ yearData.element }}) matches the {{ yearData.animal }}'s innate element ({{ yearData.fixedElement }}), {{ yearData.year }} is a year of <strong>doubled elemental energy</strong> — the {{ yearData.animal }}'s natural qualities are amplified and intensified. This can bring both enhanced strengths and exaggerated challenges.</p>
      {% elif yearData.element == "Wood" and yearData.fixedElement == "Fire" or yearData.element == "Fire" and yearData.fixedElement == "Earth" or yearData.element == "Earth" and yearData.fixedElement == "Metal" or yearData.element == "Metal" and yearData.fixedElement == "Water" or yearData.element == "Water" and yearData.fixedElement == "Wood" %}
      <p>The yearly {{ yearData.element }} element <strong>generates</strong> the {{ yearData.animal }}'s innate {{ yearData.fixedElement }} element in the productive cycle (相生). This creates a harmonious flow of energy — the Heavenly Stem supports and nourishes the animal's natural strengths.</p>
      {% else %}
      <p>The {{ yearData.element }} element interacts with the {{ yearData.animal }}'s innate {{ yearData.fixedElement }} element, creating a dynamic tension between the year's Heavenly Stem energy and the animal's core nature. Understanding this interplay is key to navigating the year's opportunities and challenges.</p>
      {% endif %}

      <p>The <strong>{{ yearData.element }} {{ yearData.animal }}</strong> carries <strong>{{ yearData.yinYang }}</strong> polarity. In Chinese cosmology, {{ yearData.yinYang }} energy represents {% if yearData.yinYang == "Yang" %}active, expansive, and outward-directed force — initiative, leadership, and bold action{% else %}receptive, inward, and reflective force — diplomacy, intuition, and careful cultivation{% endif %}.</p>

      <p>Learn more about how the Five Elements shape personality and destiny in our <a href="/wuxing/">Wu Xing encyclopaedia article</a>{% if yearData.element == "Wood" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/wood/">Wood element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Fire" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/fire/">Fire element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Earth" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/earth/">Earth element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Metal" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/metal/">Metal element page</a>{% elif yearData.element == "Water" %} and the <a href="/wuxing/water/">Water element page</a>{% endif %}.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="personality">
