    <section id="sexagenary">
      <h2>The Sexagenary Cycle Position</h2>
      <p>{{ yearData.year }} is position <strong>#{{ ((yearData.year - 4) % 60 + 60) % 60 + 1 }}</strong> in the <a href="/calendar/">sexagenary cycle</a> (六十甲子, liùshí jiǎzǐ). The cycle combines 10 Heavenly Stems with 12 Earthly Branches to produce 60 unique stem-branch pairs. Since 10 and 12 share a common factor of 2, only 60 (not 120) combinations occur.</p>
      <p>The same {{ yearData.pillarCn }} pillar last appeared in <strong>{{ yearData.year - 60 }}</strong> and will next appear in <strong>{{ yearData.year + 60 }}</strong>. The same {{ yearData.animal }} animal (but with a different element) last appeared in <strong>{{ yearData.year - 12 }}</strong> and will next appear in <strong>{{ yearData.year + 12 }}</strong>.</p>
