          <div class="faq-answer"><p>In BaZi (Four Pillars) astrology, the {{ yearData.year }} zodiac year begins at Lichun (立春, Start of Spring), typically February 3-5. The popular Chinese New Year date (between January 21 and February 20) is used in folk tradition. People born before Lichun in {{ yearData.year }} belong to the previous year's zodiac animal.</p></div>
